{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f328a83f-c900-4fc5-8596-16aa507f45c0","content":"Output: `{\"name\":\"Jane\",\"age\":30}` ✅\n\nHere's the final program:\n\n```csharp\nusing System.Text.Json;\n\nvar options = new JsonSerializerOptions { PropertyNamingPolicy = JsonNamingPolicy.CamelCase };\nvar json = JsonSerializer.Serialize(new Person(\"Jane\", 30), options);\nConsole.WriteLine(json);\n\npublic record Person(string Name, int Age);\n```\n\nThe key is `JsonNamingPolicy.CamelCase` passed via `JsonSerializerOptions` — it converts `Name` → `name` and `Age` → `age` automatically. The record must appear **after** the top-level statements (a C# requirement).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3793a439-b292-4db4-b93f-6319502322db","outputTokens":170,"requestId":"483D:B515D:B349BB:CBD612:6A027990"},"id":"5b851db9-28f5-49df-90e4-5f9674b166c4","timestamp":"2026-05-12T00:51:35.737Z","parentId":"a8a7708e-a6ef-4aed-9e17-72733190bfc2"}
